  "title": "Murex Datamart Consultant",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for an experienced Murex Datamart professional with strong technical, functional, and analytical skills. The candidate should have in-depth knowledge of the Murex Datamart architecture, hands-on experience with Unix and SQL, and strong understanding of financial product classes. The role involves Datamart development, reconciliation, reporting, performance optimization, and collaboration with front-office, risk, finance, and IT teams.<br /><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><a href=\"https://luxhire.luxoft.com/hr/browse/VR-120374#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a>• Strong end-to-end knowledge of Murex Datamart architecture and components.<br />• Design, develop, enhance, and support Murex Datamart reports<br />• Work on Datamart configuration.<br />• Handle Datamart migrations, upgrades, and version changes.<br />• Analyze and resolve Datamart data issues and performance bottlenecks.<br />• Work closely with cross-functional teams to deliver system enhancements and new product onboarding.<br /><strong></strong><br /><strong>Mandatory Skills Description:</strong><a href=\"https://luxhire.luxoft.com/hr/browse/VR-120374#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a>• 9+ Years in Murex Datamart, preferably within a banking environment.<br />• Strong understanding of Murex trade lifecycle.<br />• Functional exposure across all major product classes.<br />• Proficiency in Unix/Linux fundamentals for system operations and scripting.<br />• Should have Strong understanding of SQL for data extraction, analysis, and troubleshooting.<br />• Experience with Murex upgrades and migrations.<br />• Exposure to EOD / Batch processing.<br />• Experience supporting regulatory or finance-driven reporting.<br /><strong>Nice-to-Have Skills Description:</strong><a href=\"https://luxhire.luxoft.com/hr/browse/VR-120374#\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"></a>• Demonstrate ownership and responsibility in all assignments.<br />• Bachelor's degree in Computer Engineering/ School of Computing/ Finance IT/ other related IT degrees would be preferred<br /><br /></p><p></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",
